		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.90]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Lunarwolf&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I recently made a new monk and Im curious about practicing various weapon skills. I made the mistake of twinking my monk a little too much with good weapons, and my weapon skills could not keep up with my levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;I got to level 10 rather quickly, any my 2h2 and 1hb were at least 30 points behind max.  <br>So, note to self: don't twink monks until after 10.<br>Anyway, after skipping quest, dumping way too many practice points into weapon skills, Ive got everything caught up at level 12, except 2hb.  While I dont intend to use 2hb a lot, it doesn't hurt to have everything caught up, and there are some really nice monk 2hb's later in the game.  So, at what level is it too late to start practicing a weapon skill?  Do you think that 12 levels of unuse is too many, or will I be ok just starting now?<br><br>Thanks<br>Lunar</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >4 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
