		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=92601"><span id=Sage>Feldaer</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>254 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.60]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Feldaer&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Grab yourself an abandoned orc shovel, off the ground at the orc camp in lake rathe. It is a 2hb, and is 4dmg/27dly. Horrible weapon, but great for raising skill, especially if you have a haste item as well. The easiest thing to do is have a friend mage or necro make a pet thats blue to you, and smack the heck out of it until your skill is maxxed. Otherwise, just fight light blues, or group and only use the shovel when the mobs are well under control.<br><br>You definitely want your 2hb maxxed. Wouldn't it suck to win the roll on a t staff (or better) and not be able to use it, because your skill is too low to hit anything. Best yuo try to raise your skill now, while you can still kill light blues with the orc shovel, than to wait until you are even higher level.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Apr 19th 12:38 PM2002 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=10192235125391&num=4&page=&post=1&replyto=10192339496341"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=10192339496341></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=141592"><span id=Scholar>dabrock</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>72 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=dabrock&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Another good weapon for 2hb is the bamboo bo stick. It is very light and fast, but doesn't do much damage. The main benefits are that it won't weigh you down or run you out of stamana like many 2hb weapons, and because of it's speed it allows you to swing a lot which means you get your skill up much faster than a slow weapon. If you have a lot of extra skill points to spend you might want to sink about 10 of them into 2hb before you start training it seriously, and doing it in a group or with a partner who knows you are training it will help. You could take on blues with the other person holding the agro, healing you, or whatever the case might be based on their class.<br><br>With a bamboo bo stick and some help you should be able to get your skill up 15-20 points within 2-3 hours depending on down time. But once you get a really good 2hb weapon you will be glad you did. Especially when you are on high level raids you don't want aggro, and a hard-hitting, slow, 2hb weapon will keep aggro off you while doing more damage over time than 2 1hb weapons. <br><br>Remember, when you are fighting with a warrior and cleric you are not going to tank a lot, and if they know what they are doing they don't want you to tank a lot either, because that will mean the cleric needs to heal you more often than a warrior to keep you alive. Grab a good 2hb (like a IFS or Tstaff) and you will keep everyone happy while you inflict massive damage and yet not risk killing yourself and everyone else by pulling agro when you shouldn't.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
